Package edu.cnm.deepdive.northstarsharingclient.service

Interface NorthStarSharingWebServiceProxy

  • public interface NorthStarSharingWebServiceProxy
    An interface used by Retrofit to dynamically construct the HTTP GET and POST requests to the web service.

    • Nested Class Summary

      static class  NorthStarSharingWebServiceProxy.InstanceHolder
      A helper class to create and contain a singleton instance of the NorthStarSharingWebServiceProxy.

      • post

        @Multipart
@POST("galleries/{id}/images")
Single<Image> post​(@Header("Authorization")
                   String bearerToken,
                   @Part
                   okhttp3.MultipartBody.Part file,
                   @Part("title")
                   okhttp3.RequestBody title,
                   @Part("azimuth")
                   okhttp3.RequestBody azimuth,
                   @Part("pitch")
                   okhttp3.RequestBody pitch,
                   @Part("roll")
                   okhttp3.RequestBody roll,
                   @Part("latitude")
                   okhttp3.RequestBody latitude,
                   @Part("longitude")
                   okhttp3.RequestBody longitude,
                   @Path("id")
                   UUID id)
        POST a single Image to the web service without a description asynchronously, using a Single ReactiveX value response.
        Parameters:
        bearerToken - The Oauth2 bearer token used for authorizing the request.
        file - The Image File to be persisted.
        title - The user-entered title.
        azimuth - The azimuth of the camera at the time of the picture.
        pitch - The pitch of the camera at the time of the picture.
        roll - The roll of the camera at the time of the picture.
        latitude - The latitude of the camera at the time of the picture.
        longitude - The longitude of the camera at the time of the picture.
        id - The unique identifier for the Gallery that will contain this Image sent as a path variable.
        Returns:
        {@link Single<Image>}
